16 SECTION 2.
17 Article III of the Constitution is amended by adding at the end thereof a new Section XI to
18 read as follows:
19 "SECTION XI.
20 DIRECT INITIATIVES AND REFERENDUMS
21 Paragraph I. Power vested in the people. (a) The people of Georgia reserve to
22 themselves the power, through the process set forth in this section, to enact, repeal, or
23 amend statutes of general law which shall be known as the direct initiative and referendum
24 process.
25 (b) The people, through direct initiative and referendum, shall have the power to make
26 all general laws consistent with this Constitution, and not repugnant to the Constitution of
27 the United States, which they shall deem necessary and proper for the welfare of the state;
28 provided, however, that such power shall not extend to enacting, repealing, or amending
29 statutes:
30 (1) Relating to Section IX of this article relating to appropriations or to Article VII
31 relating to taxation and finance;
32 (2) Relating to retirement systems enacted pursuant to Section X of this article;
33 (3) Necessary for the immediate preservation of public peace, health, or safety;
34 (4) That maintain state institutions;
35 (5) Modifying procedures related to the direct initiative and referendum process
36 provided for in this section or the direct initiative process provided for in Section I of
37 Article IX;
38 (6) Relating to local legislation authorized pursuant to Paragraph VIII of Section V of
39 this article; or
