150 SECTION 4.
151 The above proposed amendment to the Constitution shall be published and submitted as
152 provided in Article X, Section I, Paragraph II of the Constitution. The ballot submitting the
153 above proposed amendment shall have written or printed thereon the following:
154 "( ) YES Shall the Constitution of Georgia be amended so as to provide that the people
155 ( ) NO of the State of Georgia shall have a limited power through direct initiative and
156 referendum petition to enact, repeal, or amend statutes and to amend this
157 Constitution?"
158 All persons desiring to vote in favor of ratifying the proposed amendment shall vote "Yes."
159 All persons desiring to vote against ratifying the proposed amendment shall vote "No." If
160 such amendment shall be ratified as provided in said Paragraph of the Constitution, it shall
161 become a part of the Constitution of this state.
